  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math alttext=\"27\"><mn>27</mn>\n</math>. It&rsquo;s given that <math alttext=\"6 percent sign\"><mn>6</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of the <math alttext=\"450\"><mn>450</mn>\n</math> tiles in a box are black. Therefore, the number of black tiles in the box can be calculated by multiplying the number of tiles in the box by <math alttext=\"StartFraction 6 Over 100 EndFraction\"><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac></math>, which is equivalent to <math alttext=\"450 left parenthesis StartFraction 6 Over 100 EndFraction right parenthesis\"><mn>450</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>, or <math alttext=\"27\"><mn>27</mn>\n</math>.</p>",
